.TH "ZAPPING_SETUP_FB" "1" 
.SH "NAME" 
zapping_setup_fb \(em  sets up the Framebuffer for zapping. 
.SH "SYNOPSIS" 
.PP 
\fBzapping_setup_fb\fP [\fB--device \fP\fIdev\fP]  [\fB--display \fP\fId\fP]  [\fB--bpp \fP\fIx\fP]  [\fB--verbose\fP]  [\fB--quiet\fP]  [\fB--help, -?\fP]  [\fB--usage\fP]  [\fB--version\fP]  
.SH "DESCRIPTION" 
.PP 
\fBzapping_setup_fb\fP is a small program intended to be 
installed as suid root that sets up the Framebuffer. If you have pam
installed, it can be pam'ified too.
.SH "PURPOSE"
Overlaying TV in the video ram requires the driver to know the
destination address in memory. To set this value root permissions are
needed, this is why \fBzapping_setup_fb\fP needs this level of
privileges. I've tried to make it secure, but better don't trust it
very much.
